In the (k + 1)-th loop, the LC-PSS searches for an optimal partition location for each layer-volume obtained in the k-th loop (line 4 to 12). The optimal partition locations found in a loop is appended to Rp‚àó (line 11). The loop stops when no more optimal partition locations are appended to Rp‚àó (line 12, 13). In the worst case, there will be (1 + |M |) ¬∑ |M |/2 loops to Ô¨Ånd the optimal partition strategy (i.e., when the optimal partition scheme is to partition the CNN model layer by layer). In contrast, if we brute-forcely search over all possible partition strategies for a CNN model M [69], there will be (|M | ¬∑ |M ‚àí 1| ¬∑ ... ¬∑ 2) loops.

