For an layer-volume splitter, the splitting parameters (decisions) (xl1, xl2, ..., xl|D|‚àí1) are non-negative integers ranging from 0 to Hl. However, due to this problem‚Äôs high search space dimension, a discrete action space has an extremely high dimension. Moreover, as the conÔ¨Ågurations vary across layers in a CNN model, the dimension of a discrete action space changes across layer-volumes. Thus, it is impractical to utilize DRL algorithms with discrete action space in the LV splitter. When applying DRL algorithms with continuous action space, the action mapping function is deÔ¨Åned:

